  <body>
    <section name="Add boolean to Documentttype">
      <span class="shortdesc">How to add a boolean to a documenttype.</span>

   <div class='screenshot'>
     <img src="../../../../images/inars/add_boolean_to_documenttype.png" alt='Add boolean to documenttype screenshot'/> 
     <p>
      Adding mandatory <a href='../concepts/boolean.html'>boolean</a> field sar:indoors with caption 'Indoors?' 
      to documenttype `upcoming'.      
     </p>
   </div>

   <p>
    Open the <a href='./goto_documenttype_tab.html'>documenttype</a> for editing. 
    In the list of possible fields, 
    click on '<a href='../concepts/boolean.html'>Boolean</a>' (far right, almost at the top, 
    Below 'Date' and Above 'hippo:resource'). 
    A <span class='index' id='checkbox'>checkbox</span> appears as part of the documenttype.
    The boolean has the value 'yes' or 'true' if the box is checked, and 'no' or 'false' if the
    box is not checked. 
   </p>
   <ul>
    <li>
     <a href='./fieldcaption.html'>Define a caption for the new field</a>.
    </li>
    <li>
     Also, <a href='./naming_a_field.html'>define a name</a> for it.
    </li>
    <li>
     Decide if it should be <a href='./mandatory_or_optional.html'>mandatory or optional</a>.
    </li>
   </ul>

